# Accessible, Secure Enhancements for Listings Page

Merging static listings with interactive filters introduces accessibility and security concerns. The page currently uses JavaScript to filter and render results, so we must ensure **accessible navigation** and **safe scripting**. Key fixes include adding a “Skip to main” link (WCAG 2.4.1)【1†L19-L27】, visible focus indicators (WCAG 2.4.7)【3†L31-L39】, and sufficient color contrast (≥4.5:1)【6†L68-L72】. We should avoid any unsafe DOM operations (the code’s `innerHTML` only clears a container, which is acceptable) and ensure all UI targets (buttons, links) meet the 24×24 CSS px minimum size【8†L142-L149】. In summary: **P0:** implement WCAG skip-link and focus styles, ensure 4.5:1 contrast and minimum target sizes. **P1:** improve keyboard behavior (e.g. form submission on Enter), add `role="status"` for toasts, and use secure link practices (`rel="noopener"` for new tabs). **P2:** review form labeling and ARIA roles, and ensure error handling. All recommendations are backed by W3C and OWASP guidelines as cited.

## Prioritized Changes (P0/P1/P2)

| Priority | Change / Feature                 | Rationale & Standards                                                         | Effort |
|:--------:|:---------------------------------|:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------|:------:|
| **P0**   | **Skip-to-content link**         | Adds a “Skip to main content” link as first focusable item【1†L19-L27】. Meets WCAG 2.4.1 (Bypass Blocks). | Med |
| **P0**   | **Visible focus indicator**      | Ensure all controls (links/buttons) have a CSS outline or style on `:focus`【3†L31-L39】. WCAG 2.4.7 requires visible focus. | Med |
| **P0**   | **Contrast ≥4.5:1**             | Text and UI elements must meet WCAG 1.4.3 contrast 【6†L68-L72】. Buttons on dark background require high contrast. | Med |
| **P0**   | **Target size ≥24×24 px**        | All interactive controls (buttons, links) should be at least 24×24 CSS px【8†L142-L149】. Improves accessibility for motor-impaired users. | Med |
| **P0**   | **Secure DOM rendering**         | Use `textContent`/DOM APIs for dynamic content. Avoid injecting raw HTML. Current code clears container safely. | Low |
| **P1**   | **Keyboard/ARIA enhancements**   | Enable pressing Enter to apply filters; add `role="status"` to toast for screen readers【1†L19-L27】. Label form controls properly (already present). | Low |
| **P1**   | **Link security**               | For any links that open in new tabs (e.g. detailed view), add `rel="noopener"`【turn2search3†L0-L3】 to prevent tabnabbing. (Internal links can stay same-window.) | Low |
| **P1**   | **Feedback and Undo**            | Provide error messages or empty-state text if no results. Ensure toast messages are accessible. Optionally allow undo of filter resets. | Low |
| **P2**   | **API Integration Placeholder**  | Code already notes where to replace static data with `GET /properties`. Ensure any future `fetch` calls check for HTTPS and handle errors. | Low |

*Thresholds:* We enforce WCAG Level AA contrast (4.5:1 for regular text)【6†L68-L72】, focus rings on all controls【3†L31-L39】, and 24px target sizes【8†L142-L149】 as per W3C guidelines. 

