**Key changes:** Added a “Skip to main content” link (Technique G1)【1†L19-L27】 and keyboard focus outlines. All interactive elements (buttons, links) remain at least 24×24 CSS px as required【8†L142-L149】. The toast has `role="status"` for accessibility. We replaced any dynamic HTML insertions with DOM methods and `textContent`. Filter inputs now accept Enter key. Toasts and buttons use clear visible styles (outline on focus)【3†L31-L39】【6†L68-L72】. We preserved existing features (filters, sort, static data) and marked where API calls would go. 

## Test Cases

- **Keyboard Navigation:** Tab through page. *Expected:* Focus outline appears on each control (skip link, filters, buttons)【3†L31-L39】; skip link jumps to main content.
- **Contrast Check:** Use a tool (e.g. WCAG Contrast Checker) on text vs. background. *Expected:* All text and UI elements meet 4.5:1 ratio【6†L68-L72】.
- **Filter Functionality:** Set filters (e.g. City=“Bangalore”, Locality=“Hoodi”) and click Apply. *Expected:* Only matching cards shown, count updates correctly.
- **Reset Button:** Click “Reset”. *Expected:* All filters clear and full list displays.
- **Enter Key Filter:** Focus on budget input and press Enter. *Expected:* Filters apply as if “Apply” clicked.
- **No Results State:** Choose filters yielding no listings (e.g. type=“Plot” and city=“Mumbai”). *Expected:* "0 results" and empty grid (possibly show a “No listings” message if added).
- **Link Security:** The “View” link opens property page; right-click "Open in new tab" should have `noopener` if implemented. *Expected:* New tab opens safely (no access to opener).
- **ARIA/Toast:** Trigger toast (click API button). *Expected:* Toast appears (role="status"), screen reader announces text.

